<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="545" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d545">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Pierrepont</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-19"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Department’s July 18. At the request of the Chilean minister for foreign
                            affairs 1 to-day handed to him a copy of the protocol. The Argentine and
                            Brazilian ministers not yet having instructions, I ventured the private
                            opinion that he could exercise a very salutary influence on Ecuador.
                            This brought forth the renewed assurance of cooperation and of desire to
                            promote peace.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pierrepont.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
